10. React.memo() 
================================
. React.memo() is used to preventing unnecessary re-renders of a component
  when its props haven't changed.

. Just wrap the component with React.memo() to implement this

. useCallback used to preventing unnecessary re-renders of a function.

--------------
Example 1:
If the props 'item' have not changed, React skips the render for the 'List' component.
--------------

import React, { useState } from "react";

